dels/game.py:42`** vs **`core/engine/order_processor.py:87-90`**:\n\n`PlayerState.round_cost()` uses module-level constants:\n```python\ndef round_cost(self) -> float:\n    return self.inventory * HOLDING_COST_PER_UNIT + self.backlog * BACKLOG_COST_PER_UNIT\n```\n\n`accrue_costs()` uses config values:\n```python\ncost = ps.inventory * state.config.holding_cost + ps.backlog * state.config.backlog_cost\n```\n\nIf `GameConfig` is created with custom costs, `round_cost()` returns wrong values silently. Delete `round_cost()` from the model and call `accrue_costs` logic consistently. Or pass config:\n\n```python\ndef round_cost(self, config: GameConfig) -> float:\n    return self.inventory * config.holding_cost + self.backlog * config.backlog_cost\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `fulfill_orders` — two loops, one would do\n\n**`core/engine/order_processor.py:23-52`** — builds `demand_by_role` dict then immediately iterates roles again. Minor, but clean-up opportunity:\n\n```python\ndef fulfill_orders(state: GameState, customer_demand: int) -> GameState:\n    roles = ROLE_ORDER\n    for i, role in enumerate(roles):\n        demand = (customer_demand if i == 0 else state.orders_this_round.get(roles[i - 1], 0))\n        ps = state.players[role]\n        total_demand = demand + ps.backlog\n        shipped = min(ps.inventory, total_demand)\n        ps.inventory -= shipped\n        ps.backlog = total_demand - shipped\n        if i > 0:\n            state.players[roles[i - 1]].incoming_shipments.append(\n                IncomingShipment(quantity=shipped, arrives_in_rounds=state.config.shipping_delay)\n            )\n    return state\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. `get_visible_state` — `model_dump()` on every WebSocket push\n\n**`core/engine/game_engine.py:95`** — fine for now, but when this runs over WebSockets at game tick rate, serializing every `IncomingShipment` per player per tick adds up. Cache the serialized form or use `__slots__`-based structs for `IncomingShipment` once the WS layer exists.\n\n---\n\n### Priority\n\n| Issue | Severity | File |\n|---|---|---|\n| `incoming_orders` never drained | **High** — real leak | `order_processor.py:72` |\n| Cost formula divergence | **High** — silent wrong values | `game.py:42` |\n| Redundant object alloc | Medium | `order_processor.py:9` |\n| Double loop in `fulfill_orders` | Low | `order_processor.py:23` |\n| `model_dump` in hot path | Low (future) | `game_engine.py:95` |\n\nItems 1 and 3 are actionable now. Want me to apply the fixes?\n",
